sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Outbound Network Connection Initiated By Script Interpreter
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a script interpreter wscript/cscript opening a network connection to a non-local network. Adversaries may use script to download malicious payloads.

match_context.values: @{SourceIsIpv6=false; DestinationPort=5506; DestinationIp=84.21.189.63; Protocol=tcp; SourceIp=192.168.122.100; DestinationIsIpv6=false; EventID=3; SourcePort=49729; Image=C:\Windows\System32\WScript.exe; Initiated=true}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects modification of the registry settings used for Internet Explorer and other Windows components that use these settings. An attacker can abuse this registry key to add a domain to the trusted sites Zone or insert JavaScript for persistence

attributes.magic: ASCII text, with CRLF line terminators

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered downloader. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/ims"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO EXE - Served Attached HTTP
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ET INFO EXE - Served Attached HTTP"; flow:to_client,established; http.header; content:"Content-Disposition"; nocase; content:"attachment"; nocase; file.data; content:"MZ"; within:2; classtype:misc-activity; sid:2014520; rev:8; metadata:created_at 2012_04_06, confidence High, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2022_11_30;)

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO Executable Download from dotted-quad Host

alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Observed UA-CPU Header"; flow:established,to_server; http.header_names; content:"|0d 0a|ua-cpu|0d 0a|"; nocase; threshold: type limit, track by_src, seconds 180, count 1; reference:url,oreilly.com/library/view/http-the-definitive/1565925092/re52.html; classtype:misc-activity; sid:2062715; rev:1; metadata:attack_target Client_Endpoint, created_at 2025_06_03, deployment Perimeter, confidence High, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2025_06_03;)

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The script initializes objects for HTTP communication, binary stream handling, and shell operations. It then performs an HTTP GET request to download a file named "toying.exe" from `http://84.21.189.63:5506/`. If the download is successful, the script saves the downloaded content to `C:\Windows\Temp\toying.exe`. Following the save operation, it executes the newly downloaded file `C:\Windows\Temp\toying.exe` in a hidden window.
